		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Image editing</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For the uses, cultural impact, and ethical concerns of image editing, see <a href="/wiki/Photo_manipulation" title="Photo manipulation">Photo manipulation</a>.</div>
<div class="dablink">For the process of culling and archiving images, see <a href="/wiki/Digital_asset_management" title="Digital asset management">Digital asset management</a>.</div>
<p><b>Image editing</b> encompasses the processes of altering <a href="/wiki/Image" title="Image">images</a>, whether they be <a href="/wiki/Digital_photography" title="Digital photography">digital photographs</a>, traditional <a href="/wiki/Photographic_processing" title="Photographic processing">analog photographs</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Illustration" title="Illustration">illustrations</a>. Traditional analog image editing is known as <a href="/wiki/Retouching" title="Retouching" class="mw-redirect">photo retouching</a>, using tools such as an <a href="/wiki/Airbrush" title="Airbrush">airbrush</a> to modify photographs, or editing illustrations with any traditional <a href="/wiki/Art_medium" title="Art medium" class="mw-redirect">art medium</a>. <a href="/wiki/Graphic_software" title="Graphic software" class="mw-redirect">Graphic software</a> programs, which can be broadly grouped into <a href="/wiki/Vector_graphics_editor" title="Vector graphics editor">vector graphics editors</a>, <a href="/wiki/Raster_graphics_editor" title="Raster graphics editor">raster graphics editors</a>, and <a href="/wiki/3d_modeler" title="3d modeler" class="mw-redirect">3d modelers</a>, are the primary tools with which a user may manipulate, enhance, and transform images. Many image editing programs are also used to <a href="/wiki/Artistic_rendering" title="Artistic rendering">render</a> or create <a href="/wiki/Computer_art" title="Computer art">computer art</a> from scratch.</p>
